<% content_for :page_header do %>
  <br />
  <ul class="breadcrumb">
    <li><%= link_to 'Documentation', root_path %> <span class="divider">/</span></li>
    <li class="active">Guides: Create a Procurement Document</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="span12">
      <h1>Creating a Procurement Document</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>

<h3>Required Information</h3>
<p>
  There is only 1 piece of information needed in order to create a Procurement Document:
</p>

<table class="table">
  <tr>
    <td>Number</td>
    <td>The Procurement Document Number (i.e. Contract Number)</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br />
<p>
  The procurement document is created using the following resource: <%= link_to 'POST procurement_documents', resources_procurement_document_procurement_document_create_path %>
</p>
<br />
<h3>Additional Information</h3>
<p>
  Once created, you will need to provide additional information about the procurement document in order for the Clause Logic Service to determine the appropriate clauses/provisions for the procurement document.
</p>
<table class="table">
  <tr>
    <td>Regulations</td>
    <td>Specify which regulations (FAR, DFARS, etc.) apply to the procurement document.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Indicators</td>
    <td>Specify details about the procurement document: Total Value, Type of Contract, Procedures Used, etc.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>
  Regulations can be specified using the following resource: <%= link_to 'PUT procurement_documents/:token/regulations', resources_procurement_document_regulations_update_path %><br />
  Indicators can be specified using the following resource: <%= link_to 'PUT procurement_documents/:token/indicators', resources_procurement_document_indicators_update_path %>
</p>
